headline: Pregnant Woman Is Strangled and Pushed Out of Car Onto a Street in Brooklyn
abstract: Tatiana Walton was found unresponsive on a Brooklyn street. Her boyfriend was later charged with murder.
lead_paragraph: Police officers answering a 911 call early on Wednesday found a woman who was unconscious and “visibly pregnant” on the ground outside an apartment house in the Red Hook section of Brooklyn, officials said. She had been pulled from a car that drove off quickly.
